A few quick code comments:<p>Now().UnixNano() is not guaranteed to be monotonically increasing. I&#x27;d be more careful if your keys really do need to be unique.<p>You can use time.Truncate to get the 10 minute interval.<p><pre><code>    var t time.Time
    t = start
    for {
    	if t.After(stop) {
    		break
    	}
    	/* ... */
    	t = t.Add(d)
    }
</code></pre>
Would usually be written:<p><pre><code>    for t := start; !t.After(stop); t = t.Add(d) {</code></pre>
